SIMPLE: tellurian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tellurian
<hw>Tel*lu"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tellus</ets>, <ets>-uris</ets>, the earth.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the earth.</def> <rj><au>De Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tellurian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tellurian
<hw>Tel*lu"ri*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A dweller on the
earth.</def> <rj><au>De Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for showing the operation of the
causes which produce the succession of day and night, and the changes of
the seasons.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>tellurion</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Telluric</ent>⟦br⟧
